  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I block Skype on Mac?",
  "response": "Blocking Skype on a Mac can be achieved through several methods, including using built-in parental controls, firewall settings, or third-party applications. Here are some ways to do it:\n\n### Using Parental Controls:\n\n1. **Open System Preferences**:\n   - Click on the Apple menu in the top-left corner of your screen.\n   - Select \"System Preferences.\"\n\n2. **Go to Screen Time**:\n   - In System Preferences, click on \"Screen Time.\"\n\n3. **Set Up Screen Time**:\n   - If Screen Time is not already set up, follow the prompts to enable it.\n\n4. **Choose the User**:\n   - Select the user account you want to manage.\n\n5. **App Limits**:\n   - Click on \"App Limits.\"\n   - Add a limit for Skype by clicking the \"+\" button, then selecting Skype from the list of applications.\n   - Set the limit to zero hours/minutes to effectively block Skype usage.\n\n### Using Firewall Settings:\n\n1. **Open System Preferences**:\n   - Click on the Apple menu in the top-left corner.\n   - Select \"System Preferences.\"\n\n2. **Security & Privacy**:\n   - Click on \"Security & Privacy.\"\n\n3. **Firewall**:\n   - Go to the \"Firewall\" tab.\n   - Click the lock icon in the bottom-left corner and enter your admin password to make changes.\n\n4. **Firewall Options**:\n   - Click on \"Firewall Options.\"\n   - Click the \"+\" button to add an application.\n   - Select Skype from the Applications folder.\n\n5. **Block Incoming Connections**:\n   - Ensure Skype is set to block incoming connections.\n\n### Using Third-Party Applications:\n\nVarious third-party applications are designed to manage and block applications on a Mac. Some popular options include:\n\n1. **Cold Turkey**:\n   - Cold Turkey is a productivity tool that can block specific apps and websites.\n   - Download and install Cold Turkey.\n   - Configure the settings to block Skype.\n\n2. **SelfControl**:\n   - SelfControl is an open-source application that can block access to specific sites and applications.\n   - Download and install SelfControl.\n   - Add Skype to the block list.\n\n### Network-Level Blocking:\n\n1. **Router Settings**:\n   - Access your router's settings page (usually by entering the router's IP address into a web browser).\n   - Look for parental controls or access restrictions.\n   - Add Skype's IP addresses or domains to the block list.\n\nBy using one or more of these methods, you should be able to effectively block Skype on your Mac.",
